cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper deals with online forecasting problems for non-convex machine learning models, which are commonly studied in the machine learning community. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The paper also introduces a novel regret framework, which is related to optimization and decision-making, and can be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of time-smoothed gradients is a technique commonly used in optimization and can be related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also uses a real-world dataset, which can be related to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
